caption.p: 1H-NMR spectra of isoliquiritin (1), liquiritigenin (2), liquiritin (3), and Glycyrrhiza uralensis Fisch. Extract (4), obtained at 600 MHz in DMSO-d 6 solvent. The quantitative signals of isoliquiritin (A), liquiritin (B), liquiritigenin (C), and dichloromethane (D) were at δ 8.187–8.172 ppm, δ 4.891–4.878 ppm, δ 6.83–6.85 ppm, and δ 5.75 ppm, respectively.
